          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A helium gas target of purity > 99.9% at 0.8 bar",
                "pressure."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BGO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma rays were detected in two arrays, each",
                "having seven close packed hexagonal bismuth germanate",
                "scintillation detectors placed ~ 3 cm above and below",
                "the target. The upper BGO detectors had a thickness",
                "of 76 mm and a face to face width of 56 mm while the",
                "corresponding numbers for the lower set were 64 and",
                "56 mm."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The two alpha particles were detected in an",
                "array of six silicon (Si) p-i-n diodes (9 mm x 9 mm x",
                "500 mu-m). These were placed at forward angles in a",
                "close packed configuration. A 300 mu-m thick Si",
                "detector was also placed at ~ 110 degree with respect",
                "to the beam and the spectra were recorded separately",
                "to monitor the impurities (mainly air) in the helium",
                "gas via their corresponding elastic peaks."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Detection of two alphas and gamma in",
                "coincidence."
              ]
            }
          ],
